{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840834947,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785cb14a001L5mbfQ2mXvlzjF","messageID":"msg_d785c95e60014X075Td7g58kjp","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775840834925,"end":1775840834946}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840834950,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785ca469001pcsRCnj5n8hjVR","messageID":"msg_d785c95e60014X075Td7g58kjp","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-002/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-002/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Define the Go types for the CodeInterpreter Custom Resource Definition (CRD).\n6: \n7: ## API Group\n8: \n9: - Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n10: - Version: `v1alpha1`\n11: - Kind: `CodeInterpreter`\n12: \n13: ## Type Definitions\n14: \n15: ### CodeInterpreter\n16: \n17: Root type representing the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n18: \n19: ### CodeInterpreterSpec\n20: \n21: Specification of the desired state for a CodeInterpreter.\n22: \n23: ### CodeInterpreterStatus\n24: \n25: Current observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n26: \n27: ## Design Decisions\n28: \n29: > TBD: Document key design decisions here.\n30: \n31: ## References\n32: \n33: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n34: - [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Go types for the CodeInterpreter Custom Resource Definition (CRD).\n\n## API Group\n\n- Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Version: `v1alpha1`\n- Kind: `CodeInterpreter`\n\n## Type Definitions\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\nRoot type representing the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n\n### CodeInterpreterSpec\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-002/design.md","time":{"start":1775840834918,"end":1775840834949}}}}
