{"type":"text","timestamp":1775840837636,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785cbe94001vIUsOHT4QDa0Sz","messageID":"msg_d785cb5bd001PkoyK0B90Rodpo","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"text","text":"Let me check AR-001 patterns and explore the existing project structure:","time":{"start":1775840837633,"end":1775840837633}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840840385,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785cc5be0012oAScYGflqsI2Q","messageID":"msg_d785cb5bd001PkoyK0B90Rodpo","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775840840373,"end":1775840840383}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840840387,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785cc4ef001Szhmd0IFSC8baf","messageID":"msg_d785cb5bd001PkoyK0B90Rodpo","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_functions.glob:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"pkg/**/*.go"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go","metadata":{"count":5,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z","time":{"start":1775840840370,"end":1775840840386}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840840397,"sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","part":{"id":"prt_d785cc003001k7S2p8Z1OkPCUt","messageID":"msg_d785cb5bd001PkoyK0B90Rodpo","sessionID":"ses_287a38ed2ffegrCZ947SUh5m24","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-001/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-001/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Design: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Define the Go types for the AgentRuntime Custom Resource Definition (CRD).\n6: \n7: ## API Group\n8: \n9: - Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n10: - Version: `v1alpha1`\n11: - Kind: `AgentRuntime`\n12: \n13: ## Type Definitions\n14: \n15: ### AgentRuntime\n16: \n17: Root type representing the AgentRuntime CRD.\n18: \n19: ### AgentRuntimeSpec\n20: \n21: Specification of the desired state for an AgentRuntime.\n22: \n23: ### AgentRuntimeStatus\n24: \n25: Current observed state of the AgentRuntime.\n26: \n27: ## Design Decisions\n28: \n29: > TBD: Document key design decisions here.\n30: \n31: ## References\n32: \n33: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n34: - [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Design: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Go types for the AgentRuntime Custom Resource Definition (CRD).\n\n## API Group\n\n- Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Version: `v1alpha1`\n- Kind: `AgentRuntime`\n\n## Type Definitions\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\nRoot type representing the AgentRuntime CRD.\n\n### AgentRuntimeSpec\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-001/design.md","time":{"start":1775840840366,"end":1775840840395}}}}
